abstracts.cdata!:
The proposed project consists of (i) the
            realignment and reconstruction to two-lane asphalt paved
            standard of the existing earth/gravel sections of the
            Ten-Zam Highway from a point 38 miles west of Morogoro to
            Mahenge (a length of 102 miles) including the Ruaha River
            bridge at Mauyuni, and from Iringa to Iyayi (a length of 125
            miles); (ii) the reconstruction to two-lane asphalt paved
            standard of the existing paved but low standard sections of
            the Tan-Zam Highway from Morogoro to a point 38 miles to the
            west and from Mahenge to Iringa (a length of 45 miles); and
            (iii) consultant's services for engineering supervision
            of the above works. Concurrently USAID is financing
            reconstruction of the highway from Iyayi to Tunduma (145
            miles) on the Zambia border. Reconstruction of the Zambia
            section of the highway from Tunduma to Kapiri Mposhi is
            being financed by the Government of Zambia, the United
            Kingdom and two loans from the Bank.
